15/01/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- EU presidency holder Slovenia will host a meeting Saturday (January 19th) of four members of the Kosovo Contact Group to discuss the future of the province, the STA news agency reported on Monday. Sources in Brussels say EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn will attend, along with EU Foreign Policy Chief Javier Solana and representatives of Britain, France, Germany and Italy. The STA says the other two Contact Group countries, Russia and the US, will not participate.
Also on Monday, Kosovo Prime Minister Hashim Thaci met with OSCE High Commissioner on National Minorities Knut Vollebaek. Thaci assured him that Kosovo will be a model state, in which the rights of all minorities would be respected. (RTK, Kosovalive, Telegrafi, Tanjug, CeskeNoviny, B92, Beta, AFP, Xinhua - 14/01/08)
